Date:  0/0/1888
Source:  Birds of New Zealand
Author:  BULLER
Vol / Page:  2/141
Edition:
Quote:  BOTAURUS POECILOPTILUS. (BLACK-BACKED BITTERN.) ... <i>Native name.</i>- Matuku-hurepo. ... [142] The Common Bittern is very generally distributed ... in places suited to its habits of life, such as raupo swamps, sedgy lagoons, and those `blind creeks', covered over with a growth of reeds ands tangle, which are so numerous in all the low districts.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1947
