Author:  POWELL
Vol / Page:  79
Edition:
Quote:  BROWN BITTERN (<i>Botaurus poiciloptilus</i>), Matuku-hurepo of the Maoris, is a bird of the swamps and lagoons throughout the country, but now less common than formerly owing to the advance of settlement.
